2.  `System.out.println(&quot;myInteger&quot; + &quot;: &quot; + myInteger);`

So, in the above example, the `$` is the *nameOf* lexical operator that converts the identified variable to a string representing the variable&#39;s name.  To be clear: I made up this syntax (including the $ token and the *nameOf* operator) to illustrate my question.  I&#39;ve used the word *nearly* because I imagine that the two token streams corresponding to the two examples I gave would not truly be identical; rather they would be *nearly* identical.  The difference being the ability to generate a compiler error if the variable isn&#39;t defined:

