Statement/expression `switch` has nothing to do with swapping elements in the array; also, the method is defined as `void` and cannot return anything;

You need to find the indexes of the `min` and `max` elements in the 2D array and then swap their contents like this:
```java
public static void switchMaxMin(int[][] twoDArray) {
    int min = min(twoDArray), max = max(twoDArray);
   
    int maxRow = -1, maxCol = -1, minRow = -1, minCol = -1;
    out:
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; twoDArray.length; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j &lt; twoDArray[i].length; j++) {
            if (twoDArray[i][j] == max &amp;&amp; maxRow == -1) {
                maxRow = i;
                maxCol = j;
            } else if (twoDArray[i][j] == min &amp;&amp; minRow == -1) {
                minRow = i;
                minCol = j;
            }
            if (minRow != -1 &amp;&amp; maxRow != -1) {
                break out;
            }
        }
    }
    arr[minRow][minCol] = max;
    arr[maxRow][maxCol] = min;
}
```
However, you may need to define additionally how to handle cases when there are _multiple_ `min` and `max` elements in the input 2D array.

